{"bill":{"bill_id":1678042,"change_hash":"ace6387abdd6f385be9fd03dfad14d98","session_id":2020,"session":{"session_id":2020,"state_id":13,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2024,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023-2024 Regular Session","session_name":"103rd General Assembly"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/IL\/bill\/HB1371\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/www.ilga.gov\/legislation\/BillStatus.asp?DocNum=1371&GAID=17&DocTypeID=HB&SessionID=112&GA=103","completed":0,"status":1,"status_date":"2023-01-24","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-24","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-31","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-15","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-22","event":10}],"state":"IL","state_id":13,"bill_number":"HB1371","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"H","body_id":35,"current_body":"H","current_body_id":35,"title":"SCH CD-JUNIOR COLOR GUARD","description":"Amends the School Code. Provides that subject to the availability of local resources, beginning with the 2024-2025 school year, each public middle school, junior high school, and high school shall establish a junior color guard program to promote the value of and honor military personnel. Provides that the junior color guard shall be used at school events, including interscholastic athletic events and other events in which the presenting of the colors is requested. Provides that each school shall allow the junior color guard to participate in community events in which the presenting of the colors may be requested. Provides that each school may work with a civic organization or association to provide adequate training to the members of the junior color guard on the execution of their duties.","pending_committee_id":0,"committee":[],"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-31","committee_id":235,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":35,"name":"Rules"},{"date":"2023-02-15","committee_id":3300,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":35,"name":"Elementary & Secondary Education: School Curriculum & Policies"}],"history